hackathon-description-text: On April 17-18, 2015, tons of hackers will travel from colleges around the nation to Lexington, KY in order to flesh out ideas in the field of technology.
hackathon-eligibility:
To participate in CatHacks, you must be a student at an American college or university.
To submit, you must be present at CatHacks during the competition weekend, April 17-18, 2015.
hackathon-requirements:
As judging will take place in person, you need only submit a brief description of your project. A paragraph or two will suffice.
Please include screenshots or pictures if possible.
hackathon-rules: CatHacks follows the MLH Code of Conduct. In order to participate, you must fill out a waiver. More information will be provided before the hackathon begins.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Pebble Watches for each team member
$50 Amazon.com Gift Cards for each team member
Raspberry Pi Version 2 for each team member

hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Lexmark: Best Project by a Female Engineer

hackathon-description-header: CatHacks is the University of Kentucky's first national hackathon.
